Ray Davies, singer and songwriter, and lead singer of The Kinks

Ray Davies, singer and songwriter, and lead singer of The Kinks.

Pictured in the 1980s, circa 1984.

Location unknown, but possibly North London, Crouch End and Highgate area where he has always lives and has a recording studio called The Konk.

Sir Raymond Douglas Davies, CBE (born 21 June 1944) is an English singer, songwriter and musician. He is the lead singer, rhythm guitarist and main songwriter for the Kinks, which he leads with his younger brother, Dave. He has also acted, directed and produced shows for theatre and television

The Kinks enjoyed several hits like Sunny Afternoon and Waterloo Sunset in the 1960s, and Lola in 1970s. The 1980s saw a revival with the hit song Come Dancing.
